As described in the [documentation][1], `fixedDelay` defines a period in milliseconds between the end of the last invocation and the start of the next.

  [1]: https://docs.spring.io/spring-framework/docs/current/javadoc-api/org/springframework/scheduling/annotation/Scheduled.html#fixedDelay--

In your case, it basically sets it to every 5 days:

 - 3600: this is the number of seconds in an hour;
 - 1000: this turns the seconds into milliseconds;
 - 24: number of hours in a day;
 - 5: number of days.

You could also set it as `432000000` (which is the result of `1000 * 3600 * 24 * 5`) but it is way harder to read.

