After some study I figured out that in order to support shared subscription, we need to implements MqqtCallback interface and override the method(mainly the method &quot;messageArrived&quot;), and then while instantiating &#39;AWSIotMqttClient&#39;, we need to set the custom callback implementation to the client object. Below is the code you can follow. You can also refer [this][1].

````
public void messageArrived(String topicStr, MqttMessage arg1) throws Exception {
            AWSIotMessage message = new AWSIotMessage(topicStr, AWSIotQos.valueOf(arg1.getQos()), arg1.getPayload());
            //client.dispatch(message);
            boolean matches = false;
            for (String topicFilter : client.getSubscriptions().keySet()) {
                if (topicFilterMatch(topicFilter, message.getTopic())) {
                    final AWSIotTopic topic = client.getSubscriptions().get(topicFilter);
                    scheduleTask(new Runnable() {
                        @Override
                        public void run() {
                            topic.onMessage(message);
                        }
                    });
                    matches = true;
                }
            }
            if (!matches) {
                System.out.println(&quot;Unexpected message received from topic &quot; + message.getTopic());
                //LOGGER.warning(&quot;Unexpected message received from topic &quot; + message.getTopic());
            }
        }
````

````
public boolean topicFilterMatch(String topicFilter, String topic) {
        if (topicFilter == null || topic == null) {
            return false;
        }
        if (topicFilter.startsWith(&quot;$share/&quot;)) {
            topicFilter = topicFilter.replaceFirst(&quot;\\$share/&quot;, &quot;&quot;);
            topicFilter = topicFilter.substring(topicFilter.indexOf(&#39;/&#39;) + 1);
        }
        String[] filterTokens = topicFilter.split(&quot;/&quot;);
        String[] topicTokens = topic.split(&quot;/&quot;);
        if (filterTokens.length &gt; topicTokens.length) {
            return false;
        }
        for (int i = 0; i &lt; filterTokens.length; i++) {
            if (filterTokens[i].equals(&quot;#&quot;)) {
                // &#39;#&#39; must be the last character
                return ((i + 1) == filterTokens.length);
            }
            if (!(filterTokens[i].equals(topicTokens[i]) || filterTokens[i].equals(&quot;+&quot;))) {
                return false;
            }
        }
        return (filterTokens.length == topicTokens.length);
    }
````

